Usage: codd init [OPTIONS]

  Initialize CoDD in a project directory.

Options:
  --project-name TEXT  Name of the project
  --language TEXT      Primary language (python/typescript/javascript/go —
                       full support; java — symbols only)
  --dest TEXT          Destination directory (default: current dir)
  --requirements PATH  Import a requirements file (any format: .md, .txt,
                       .doc). CoDD adds frontmatter automatically.
  --config-dir TEXT    Name of the CoDD config directory (default: codd). Use
                       .codd when codd/ is your source directory.
  --help               Show this message and exit.
